      "span_text": "In the SWL class, two points out of ten present positive anomalies: Bulgaria (2011 Bulgaria ( −2012 and Spain (2014 Spain ( -2015 . Grain maize in Bulgaria registered a significantly increased harvested area: it shifted from an average of 309Mha in the period 2007-2011 to an average of 442Mha of the period 2012-2016. In 2012, Bulgaria recorded +18% in production thanks to the area extension, but yield anomalies for the same year result around −16% compared with the five years average due to the severe drought [CITATION_1] , in line with the AOC analysis interpretation."
